Turkish Loans Contract After Central Bank’s Measures

-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 
2011-09-12T09:27:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/turkish-loans-contract-after-central-bank-s-measures-correct-.html
(Corrects decrease, size and scope in lead paragraph.)  Turkish loans contracted 0.7
percent in the week to Sept. 2, the biggest weekly fall since
Jan. 7, after the central bank took measures to slow lending
growth, according to data published on the banking regulator’s
website in Ankara today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Bentley at 
 mbentley3@bloomberg.net  